HEADWORD: Calorescence
<hw>Cal`o*res"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>calor</ets> heat.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The conversion
of obscure radiant heat into light; the transmutation of rays of heat
into others of higher refrangibility.</def>
<rj><au>Tyndall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

